title: For Sale:  Mossberg 500AB 12 gauge w/scope 6 shot pump shotgun 30" barrel
postcontent:
This is the Mossberg 500AB, with a picatinny rail mounted Red Dot scope. The 500AB is the 500A Mossberg shotgun with some upgrades...specifically a Walnut stock VS the various hardwood stocks found on the regular 500A model. This 500AB also has some metal etchings ,as seen in 1 photo, that the 500A doesnt have ...and it has a 30" barrel. (Every part on this 500AB is interchangeable with the regular 500A)
This is a fixed full choke 30" barreled shotgun. 30 inches is a long range shotgun. Perfect for Deer and Water Fowl...and predators of any nature. You get the 75-100 yard reach of a rifle, with the spread pattern of a shotgun.  Full choke means it keeps it's shot pattern tight over a long distance, so you get killing/stopping power at rifle like distances.  It shoots bird and buck shot...and rifled slugs. It is chambered for 2 and 3/4" and 3.00" shells.  It functions flawlessly and it looks good. The bore is beautiful inside...slick as a whistle.  It also has a metal safety switch, not a plastic one like the newer Mossbergs. It has a Tasco Red Dot scope, a good one, that enables quick sholdering and accurate firing of shotgun. For those folks who don't know what a Red Dot scope is: You turn the switch on and the red dot is displayed in the scope lens...when you look thru the scope, wherever the dot is - is where the bullet goes. If you move your head, the red dot stays on the target your pointing at and you can still see the dot as you move your head around. It makes for very quick and accurate shooting). I love this shotgun, and the new owner will too. I need money, I have to sell it. 300.00 is my negotiated price.

Saiga 7.62x39 20 round Polymer magazine with bolt hold open feature on last round. Proudly made in USA by SGM Tactical (Formerly Surefire Gun Mags) and counts as 3 component US parts for 922r Compliance Purposes.

Must be used in a 922r Compliant rifle:
The Saiga Rifle out of the box is not compliant with magazines in excess of 10 rounds. For 922r compliance parts, you must bring the foreign parts count down to ten or less with use of a magazine in excess of 10 rounds in a Saiga rifle. The stock Saiga has 11 foreign parts with use of a high capacity magazine, so only one foreign part needs to be removed to stay compliant. The easiest way to make your stock Saiga rifle compliant with high capacity magazines is to change out the gas piston, forearm, or buttstock.

This example was made in ~1992 during a time when S&W was known to really have their stuff together as far as materials and craftsmanship went.
